Here are the MSTest patterns for each scenario:

**1. Windows-only tests — platform check**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
// Or, if using bare MSTest without a helper attribute:
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");

    // ... registry code ...
}
```

**2. Skip in CI — environment-based condition**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU");

    // ... GPU code ...
}
```

Then filter in CI: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

**3. Flaky external API — retry with `[Timeout]`**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Timeout(10_000)]   // fail fast if the API hangs
[RetryFailedTest(maxRetries: 3)]   // MSTest 3.x+; retries on failure
public void WeatherApiTest()
{
    var result = CallWeatherApi();
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

> `[RetryFailedTest]` was added in **MSTest v3.8**. On older versions, use `[DataTestMethod]` with a manual retry loop, or the `[Retry]` attribute from `MSTest.TestFramework` v3.x.

**4. Cleanup even on failure — `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`**

```csharp
private string? _tempFile;

[TestInitialize]
public void Setup()
{
    _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
}

[TestCleanup]   // runs even if the test throws
public void Cleanup()
{
    if (_tempFile != null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
}

[TestMethod]
public void TempFileTest()
{
    File.WriteAllText(_tempFile!, "data");
    // ... assertions ...
}
```

**Combining them all in one class:**

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class IntegrationTests
{
    private string? _tempFile;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup() => _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (_tempFile is not null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void RegistryTest()
    {
        if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
            Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
        // ...
    }

    [TestMethod]
    [TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
    public void GpuTest()
    {
        if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
            Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI");
        // ...
    }

    [TestMethod]
    [Timeout(10_000)]
    [RetryFailedTest(3)]
    public void WeatherApiTest() { /* ... */ }
}
```

**Key takeaways:**

| Scenario | Primary mechanism |
|---|---|
| Platform gate | `Assert.Inconclusive()` / OS-condition attribute |
| CI skip | `[TestCategory]` + filter, or env-var check |
| Flaky retry | `[RetryFailedTest(n)]` (MSTest ≥ 3.8) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` (runs after every test, pass or fail) |
